  "headline": "POWERED (N=57) result, all 3 models incl. non-Anthropic GPT-4.1, 0 errors. H1 (raw vs no_signal): SIGNIFICANT at lambda>=0.5 (lam=0.5 +0.13..+0.17 p<=.007; lam=0.8 +0.31..+0.37 p~0) -> raw calibrated confidence robustly HELPS routing over no signal when verification is costly (registered SUPPORT confirmed). H2 (interface vs raw): at lambda=0.5 SIGNIFICANTLY NEGATIVE for Sonnet (-0.094 p=.029) and Opus (-0.123 p=.016); at lambda=0.8 strongly negative for ALL three (-0.23..-0.30 p~0) -> the calibrated reliability INTERFACE does not just fail to beat raw, it is significantly WORSE at meaningful verification cost (over-verification), even under held-out calibration (registered null/negative confirmed and sharpened). Effect is lambda-dependent (interface ~neutral/slightly helps at low cost lambda=0.2, significantly hurts at lambda>=0.5). Holm-Bonferroni: 22/36 secondary contrasts significant. The N-expansion from 14 to 57 moved the conclusion from 'directionally consistent, not significant' to statistically established."
}